# music-content-models

## Core Data Models

### Artist Model
Key fields:
- UUID and platform-specific IDs (Spotify, Apple Music, etc.)
- Verification status and platform links 
- Genre classifications and tags
- Engagement metrics per platform
- Connected release and event catalogs
- Rights management status

### Release Model 
Key fields:
- ISRC/UPC identifiers
- Distribution platform mappings
- Rights holders and splits
- Pre-save campaign configuration
- Cross-platform smart links
- Geographic availability rules

### Event Model
Fields:
- Venue capacity and tier configuration
- Presale code generation rules
- Geographic targeting parameters
- Marketing automation triggers
- Revenue projections per tier
- Ticket allocation rules

## Distribution Workflows

1. Release Distribution Pipeline:
```
Content Upload -> Rights Verification -> Platform Distribution -> Smart Link Generation -> Marketing Automation
```

2. Artist Verification Flow:
```
Profile Creation -> Platform Link Verification -> Rights Documentation -> Manual Review -> Status Update
```

3. Event Marketing Flow: 
```
Event Creation -> Presale Setup -> Geographic Targeting -> Automation Rules -> Cross-Channel Promotion
```

## Platform Integrations

- Spotify: Artist profile sync, release distribution, metrics aggregation
- Apple Music: Catalog management, smart links, territory rules
- Soundcloud: Creator profile sync, release uploads
- YouTube Music: Content ID matching, artist channel linking

